{"article_id":"1Ao4Kuh0Jpv4Xekb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A federal appeals court ruled Thursday against a central provision of the Defense of Marriage Act , a groundbreaking decision","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that tees up a potential battle before the Supreme Court .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"The three-judge panel of the 1st U.S . Circuit Court of Appeals in Boston ruled","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that the provision","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"defining marriage as between a man and woman","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"is unconstitutional","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"in that it denies gay couples the rights","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"granted to heterosexual couples .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The unanimous decision once again brings the issue of gay marriage to the fore of the nation 's political debate .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"It comes","depth":4},{"id":10,"text":"just a few weeks after President Obama announced his support for gay marriage","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"-- in the wake of that announcement , some gay advocacy groups have stepped up pressure on Washington","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"to fight DOMA .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Considering the potential Supreme Court battle ahead ,","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"White House Press Secretary Jay Carney was asked Thursday","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"whether the Obama administration would actively fight for overturning the law ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"which was originally signed by Democratic President Bill Clinton .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Carney noted","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"that the Obama administration has concluded","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"the section in question is unconstitutional","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"and will no longer defend it in court .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Without commenting on what steps the administration might take in the future ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"he described the Justice Department as an `` active participant '' in the case .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"`` There 's no question","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that this is in concert with the president 's views , ''","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"`` I ca n't predict what the next steps will be","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"in handling cases of this nature . ''","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Gay marriage advocates hailed Thursday 's decision ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"while its opponents condemned it .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"`` Society should protect and strengthen marriage ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"not undermine it .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"The federal Defense of Marriage Act provides that type of protection ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"and we trust","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"the U.S. Supreme Court will reverse the 1st Circuit 's erroneous decision , ''","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"said a statement from Alliance Defense Fund Legal Counsel Dale Schowengerdt .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"The court did n't rule on the law 's more politically combustible provision ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"which said","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"states","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"without same-sex marriage","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"can not be forced to recognize gay unions","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"performed in states","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"where it 's legal .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"It also was n't asked to address","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"whether gay couples have a constitutional right","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"to marry .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"The law was passed at a time","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"when it appeared Hawaii would legalize gay marriage .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Since then , many states have instituted their own bans on gay marriage ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"while eight states have approved it ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"led by Massachusetts in 2004 .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"The court , the first federal appeals panel","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"to deem the benefits section of the law unconstitutional ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"agreed with a lower level judge","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"who ruled in 2010","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that the law interferes with the right of a state","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"to define marriage","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"and denies married gay couples federal benefits","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"given to heterosexual married couples ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"including the ability","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"to file joint tax returns .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"The 1st Circuit said","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"its ruling would n't be enforced","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"until the U.S. Supreme Court decides the case ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"meaning that same-sex married couples will not be eligible to receive the economic benefits","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"denied by DOMA","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"until the high court rules .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"That 's because the ruling only applies to states within the circuit ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"including Massachusetts , Rhode Island , Maine , New Hampshire and Puerto Rico .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"Only the Supreme Court has the final say","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"in deciding","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"whether a law","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"passed by Congress","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"is unconstitutional .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"Although most Americans live in states","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"where the law still is that marriage can only be the union of a man and a woman ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"the power","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"to define marriage","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"had always been left to the individual states","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"before Congress passed DOMA ,","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"the appeals court said in its ruling .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"`` One virtue of federalism is that it permits this diversity of governance","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"based on local choice ,","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"but this applies as well to the states","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"that have chosen to legalize same-sex marriage , ''","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"Judge Michael Boudin wrote for the court .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"`` Under current Supreme Court authority , Congress ' denial of federal benefits to same-sex couples","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"lawfully married in Massachusetts","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"has not been adequately supported by any permissible federal interest . ''","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"During arguments before the court last month , a lawyer for gay married couples said","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"the law amounts to `` across-the-board disrespect . ''","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"The couples argued","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"that the power","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"to define and regulate marriage","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"had been left to the states for more than 200 years","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"before Congress passed DOMA .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"An attorney","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"defending the law","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"argued","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that Congress had a rational basis","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"for passing it in 1996 ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"when opponents worried","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"that states would be forced to recognize gay marriages","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"performed elsewhere .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"The group said","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Congress wanted to preserve a traditional and uniform definition of marriage","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"and has the power","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"to define terms","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"used to federal statutes","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"to distribute federal benefits .","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"Since DOMA was passed in 1996 ,","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"many states have instituted their own bans on gay marriage .","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"The eight states","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"that have approved gay marriage","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"are Massachusetts , Connecticut , New York , Iowa , New Hampshire , Vermont , Maryland and Washington state .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"The District of Columbia has also has approved it .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Maryland and Washington 's laws are not yet in effect","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"and may be subject to referendums .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"Last year , Obama announced","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"the U.S. Department of Justice would no longer defend the constitutionality of the law .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"After that , House Speaker John Boehner convened the Bipartisan Legal Advisory Group","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"to defend it .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"The legal group argued the case before the appeals court .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"Gay & Lesbian Advocates & Defenders , the Boston-based legal group","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"that brought one of the lawsuits on behalf of gay married couples ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"the law takes one group of legally married people","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"and treats them as `` a different class ''","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"by making them ineligible for benefits","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"given to other married couples .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"`` We 've been working on this issue for so many years ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"and for the court to acknowledge","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"that yes , same-sex couples are legally married , just as any other couple , is fantastic and extraordinary , ''","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"said Lee Swislow , GLAD 's executive director .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"Two of the three judges","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"who decided the case Thursday","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"were Republican appointees ,","depth":4},{"id":137,"text":"while the other was a Democratic appointee .","depth":3},{"id":138,"text":"Boudin was appointed by President George H.W . Bush ,","depth":4},{"id":139,"text":"while Judge Juan Torruella was appointed by President Ronald Reagan .","depth":4},{"id":140,"text":"Chief Judge Sandra Lynch is an appointee of President Bill Clinton .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":281,"left":274,"right":280,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":153,"right":273,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":149,"right":152,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":8,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":142,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":2,"right":146,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":144,"right":145,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":143,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":9,"right":151,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":10,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":167,"right":272,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":156,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":13,"right":155,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":14,"right":154,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":154,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":159,"right":165,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS